      • getConceptTerm

        public InequalityTerm getConceptTerm(java.lang.Object object)
        Return the property term for the given object. If the given object is null or a property term itself, it returns the given object. Otherwise, it checks its cache if a term object was created previously. Returns the property term if it is found; otherwise, it creates and caches a new property term before returning it.
        Specified by:
        getConceptTerm in interface ConceptTermFactory
        Parameters:

        Returns:
